From: "claude[bot]" <41898282+claude[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 08:03:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] fix(error-handling): surface gh API failures instead of
 mapping to NONE
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The two priority-extraction scripts swallowed every gh-API error
(`2>/dev/null` followed by `|| echo NONE`) and reported "no fix needed"
indistinguishably from a successful clean review. A transient 5xx, an
auth blip, or a rate-limit on the Sunday-morning 12-area burst could
silently demote a real review to skipped — bugs the reviewer flagged
would never reach the fix stage.

Fix: add a shared lib.sh with `gh_with_retry` (3 attempts, 1s/2s
backoff) and rewrite both scripts to fail loudly when the API call
itself errors. The `NONE` default is now reserved for the legitimate
"the API succeeded but no MAXIMUM_FIX_PRIORITY token was present"
case.

Addresses items 1, 2, 8 from review issue: review(error-handling):
findings — 2026-05-10.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
